{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1114,"text":"So over the past few centuries,\nmicroscopes have revolutionized our world."},{"time":9036,"text":"They revealed to us a tiny world\nof objects, life and structures"},{"time":14252,"text":"that are too small for us\nto see with our naked eyes."},{"time":17158,"text":"They are a tremendous contribution\nto science and technology."},{"time":20177,"text":"Today I'd like to introduce you\nto a new type of microscope,"},{"time":23404,"text":"a microscope for changes."},{"time":25982,"text":"It doesn't use optics\nlike a regular microscope"},{"time":28884,"text":"to make small objects bigger,"},{"time":30881,"text":"but instead it uses a video camera\nand image processing"},{"time":35257,"text":"to reveal to us the tiniest motions\nand color changes in objects and people,"},{"time":40513,"text":"changes that are impossible\nfor us to see with our naked eyes."},{"time":44355,"text":"And it lets us look at our world\nin a completely new way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48475,"text":"So what do I mean by color changes?"},{"time":50385,"text":"Our skin, for example,\nchanges its color very slightly"},{"time":53217,"text":"when the blood flows under it."},{"time":55214,"text":"That change is incredibly subtle,"},{"time":57611,"text":"which is why, when you\nlook at other people,"},{"time":59674,"text":"when you look at the person\nsitting next to you,"},{"time":61925,"text":"you don't see their skin\nor their face changing color."},{"time":65500,"text":"When we look at this video of Steve here,\nit appears to us like a static picture,"},{"time":69860,"text":"but once we look at this video\nthrough our new, special microscope,"},{"time":73720,"text":"suddenly we see\na completely different image."},{"time":76320,"text":"What you see here are small changes\nin the color of Steve's skin,"},{"time":80250,"text":"magnified 100 times\nso that they become visible."},{"time":84686,"text":"We can actually see a human pulse."},{"time":87953,"text":"We can see how fast\nSteve's heart is beating,"},{"time":91180,"text":"but we can also see the actual way\nthat the blood flows in his face."},{"time":96544,"text":"And we can do that not just\nto visualize the pulse,"},{"time":99175,"text":"but also to actually \nrecover our heart rates,"},{"time":102646,"text":"and measure our heart rates."},{"time":104439,"text":"And we can do it with regular cameras\nand without touching the patients."},{"time":108892,"text":"So here you see the pulse and heart rate\nwe extracted from a neonatal baby"},{"time":114509,"text":"from a video we took\nwith a regular DSLR camera,"},{"time":117390,"text":"and the heart rate measurement we get"},{"time":119206,"text":"is as accurate as the one you'd get\nwith a standard monitor in a hospital."},{"time":124017,"text":"And it doesn't even have to be\na video we recorded."},{"time":126659,"text":"We can do it essentially\nwith other videos as well."},{"time":129654,"text":"So I just took a short clip\nfrom \"Batman Begins\" here"},{"time":133555,"text":"just to show Christian Bale's pulse."},{"time":135459,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":137281,"text":"And you know, presumably\nhe's wearing makeup,"},{"time":139404,"text":"the lighting here is kind of challenging,"},{"time":141357,"text":"but still, just from the video,\nwe're able to extract his pulse"},{"time":144308,"text":"and show it quite well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146326,"text":"So how do we do all that?"},{"time":148246,"text":"We basically analyze the changes\nin the light that are recorded"},{"time":152844,"text":"at every pixel in the video over time,"},{"time":155115,"text":"and then we crank up those changes."},{"time":156913,"text":"We make them bigger\nso that we can see them."},{"time":159075,"text":"The tricky part is that those signals,"},{"time":160977,"text":"those changes that we're after,\nare extremely subtle,"},{"time":163910,"text":"so we have to be very careful\nwhen you try to separate them"},{"time":166689,"text":"from noise that always exists in videos."},{"time":170520,"text":"So we use some clever\nimage processing techniques"},{"time":173515,"text":"to get a very accurate measurement\nof the color at each pixel in the video,"},{"time":177509,"text":"and then the way the color\nchanges over time,"},{"time":180179,"text":"and then we amplify those changes."},{"time":182872,"text":"We make them bigger to create those types\nof enhanced videos, or magnified videos,"},{"time":186852,"text":"that actually show us those changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189024,"text":"But it turns out we can do that\nnot just to show tiny changes in color,"},{"time":193262,"text":"but also tiny motions,"},{"time":195503,"text":"and that's because the light\nthat gets recorded in our cameras"},{"time":199079,"text":"will change not only if the color\nof the object changes,"},{"time":201889,"text":"but also if the object moves."},{"time":204257,"text":"So this is my daughter\nwhen she was about two months old."},{"time":207893,"text":"It's a video I recorded\nabout three years ago."},{"time":210892,"text":"And as new parents, we all want\nto make sure our babies are healthy,"},{"time":214100,"text":"that they're breathing,\nthat they're alive, of course."},{"time":216642,"text":"So I too got one of those baby monitors"},{"time":218784,"text":"so that I could see my daughter\nwhen she was asleep."},{"time":221253,"text":"And this is pretty much what you'll see\nwith a standard baby monitor."},{"time":224780,"text":"You can see the baby's sleeping, but \nthere's not too much information there."},{"time":228474,"text":"There's not too much we can see."},{"time":230078,"text":"Wouldn't it be better,\nor more informative, or more useful,"},{"time":232902,"text":"if instead we could look\nat the view like this."},{"time":235892,"text":"So here I took the motions\nand I magnified them 30 times,"},{"time":242248,"text":"and then I could clearly see that my\ndaughter was indeed alive and breathing."},{"time":246074,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":248327,"text":"Here is a side-by-side comparison."},{"time":250249,"text":"So again, in the source video,\nin the original video,"},{"time":252732,"text":"there's not too much we can see,"},{"time":254368,"text":"but once we magnify the motions,\nthe breathing becomes much more visible."},{"time":258075,"text":"And it turns out, there's\na lot of phenomena"},{"time":260145,"text":"we can reveal and magnify\nwith our new motion microscope."},{"time":263768,"text":"We can see how our veins and arteries\nare pulsing in our bodies."},{"time":268332,"text":"We can see that our eyes\nare constantly moving"},{"time":270960,"text":"in this wobbly motion."},{"time":272847,"text":"And that's actually my eye,"},{"time":274356,"text":"and again this video was taken\nright after my daughter was born,"},{"time":277421,"text":"so you can see I wasn't getting\ntoo much sleep. (Laughter)"},{"time":281623,"text":"Even when a person is sitting still,"},{"time":284339,"text":"there's a lot of information\nwe can extract"},{"time":286383,"text":"about their breathing patterns,\nsmall facial expressions."},{"time":289912,"text":"Maybe we could use those motions"},{"time":291537,"text":"to tell us something about\nour thoughts or our emotions."},{"time":294691,"text":"We can also magnify small\nmechanical movements,"},{"time":297946,"text":"like vibrations in engines,"},{"time":299501,"text":"that can help engineers detect\nand diagnose machinery problems,"},{"time":303193,"text":"or see how our buildings and structures\nsway in the wind and react to forces."},{"time":307931,"text":"Those are all things that our society\nknows how to measure in various ways,"},{"time":312512,"text":"but measuring those motions is one thing,"},{"time":314965,"text":"and actually seeing those\nmotions as they happen"},{"time":317241,"text":"is a whole different thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319795,"text":"And ever since we discovered\nthis new technology,"},{"time":322836,"text":"we made our code available online so that \nothers could use and experiment with it."},{"time":326789,"text":"It's very simple to use."},{"time":328664,"text":"It can work on your own videos."},{"time":330708,"text":"Our collaborators at Quanta Research\neven created this nice website"},{"time":333901,"text":"where you can upload your videos\nand process them online,"},{"time":336579,"text":"so even if you don't have any experience\nin computer science or programming,"},{"time":340395,"text":"you can still very easily experiment\nwith this new microscope."},{"time":343331,"text":"And I'd like to show you\njust a couple of examples"},{"time":345735,"text":"of what others have done with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348470,"text":"So this video was made by\na YouTube user called Tamez85."},{"time":353787,"text":"I don't know who that user is,"},{"time":355250,"text":"but he, or she, used our code"},{"time":357595,"text":"to magnify small belly\nmovements during pregnancy."},{"time":361310,"text":"It's kind of creepy."},{"time":362912,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":364525,"text":"People have used it to magnify\npulsing veins in their hands."},{"time":369486,"text":"And you know it's not real science\nunless you use guinea pigs,"},{"time":373268,"text":"and apparently this guinea pig\nis called Tiffany,"},{"time":376658,"text":"and this YouTube user claims\nit is the first rodent on Earth"},{"time":379607,"text":"that was motion-magnified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382295,"text":"You can also do some art with it."},{"time":384483,"text":"So this video was sent to me\nby a design student at Yale."},{"time":387501,"text":"She wanted to see\nif there's any difference"},{"time":389638,"text":"in the way her classmates move."},{"time":391160,"text":"She made them all stand still,\nand then magnified their motions."},{"time":395369,"text":"It's like seeing \nstill pictures come to life."},{"time":398747,"text":"And the nice thing with \nall those examples"},{"time":401180,"text":"is that we had nothing to do with them."},{"time":403476,"text":"We just provided this new tool,\na new way to look at the world,"},{"time":407330,"text":"and then people find other interesting,\nnew and creative ways of using it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412462,"text":"But we didn't stop there."},{"time":414226,"text":"This tool not only allows us\nto look at the world in a new way,"},{"time":417477,"text":"it also redefines what we can do"},{"time":419845,"text":"and pushes the limits of what\nwe can do with our cameras."},{"time":423026,"text":"So as scientists, we started wondering,"},{"time":425255,"text":"what other types of physical phenomena\nproduce tiny motions"},{"time":429040,"text":"that we could now use\nour cameras to measure?"},{"time":431943,"text":"And one such phenomenon\nthat we focused on recently is sound."},{"time":435944,"text":"Sound, as we all know,\nis basically changes"},{"time":438049,"text":"in air pressure that\ntravel through the air."},{"time":440232,"text":"Those pressure waves hit objects\nand they create small vibrations in them,"},{"time":443853,"text":"which is how we hear\nand how we record sound."},{"time":446385,"text":"But it turns out that sound\nalso produces visual motions."},{"time":450053,"text":"Those are motions\nthat are not visible to us"},{"time":452886,"text":"but are visible to a camera\nwith the right processing."},{"time":455887,"text":"So here are two examples."},{"time":457460,"text":"This is me demonstrating\nmy great singing skills."},{"time":461064,"text":"(Singing)"},{"time":462698,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":464134,"text":"And I took a high-speed video\nof my throat while I was humming."},{"time":467120,"text":"Again, if you stare at that video,"},{"time":468884,"text":"there's not too much\nyou'll be able to see,"},{"time":470960,"text":"but once we magnify the motions 100 times,\nwe can see all the motions and ripples"},{"time":475292,"text":"in the neck that are involved\nin producing the sound."},{"time":478566,"text":"That signal is there in that video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481306,"text":"We also know that singers\ncan break a wine glass"},{"time":483976,"text":"if they hit the correct note."},{"time":485439,"text":"So here, we're going to play a note"},{"time":487204,"text":"that's in the resonance\nfrequency of that glass"},{"time":489730,"text":"through a loudspeaker that's next to it."},{"time":491778,"text":"Once we play that note\nand magnify the motions 250 times,"},{"time":496197,"text":"we can very clearly see \nhow the glass vibrates"},{"time":498535,"text":"and resonates in response to the sound."},{"time":502105,"text":"It's not something you're used\nto seeing every day."},{"time":504525,"text":"But this made us think.\nIt gave us this crazy idea."},{"time":508054,"text":"Can we actually invert this process\nand recover sound from video"},{"time":513662,"text":"by analyzing the tiny vibrations\nthat sound waves create in objects,"},{"time":517697,"text":"and essentially convert those\nback into the sounds that produced them."},{"time":522474,"text":"In this way, we can turn\neveryday objects into microphones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526931,"text":"So that's exactly what we did."},{"time":529163,"text":"So here's an empty bag of chips\nthat was lying on a table,"},{"time":531979,"text":"and we're going to turn that \nbag of chips into a microphone"},{"time":534804,"text":"by filming it with a video camera"},{"time":536395,"text":"and analyzing the tiny motions\nthat sound waves create in it."},{"time":539623,"text":"So here's the sound\nthat we played in the room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542419,"text":"(Music: \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550007,"text":"And this is a high-speed video\nwe recorded of that bag of chips."},{"time":553032,"text":"Again it's playing."},{"time":554306,"text":"There's no chance you'll be able\nto see anything going on in that video"},{"time":557648,"text":"just by looking at it,"},{"time":558706,"text":"but here's the sound we were able\nto recover just by analyzing"},{"time":561690,"text":"the tiny motions in that video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563873,"text":"(Music: \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580985,"text":"I call it -- Thank you."},{"time":582471,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":589878,"text":"I call it the visual microphone."},{"time":592223,"text":"We actually extract audio signals\nfrom video signals."},{"time":595613,"text":"And just to give you a sense\nof the scale of the motions here,"},{"time":598799,"text":"a pretty loud sound will cause that bag\nof chips to move less than a micrometer."},{"time":604135,"text":"That's one thousandth of a millimeter."},{"time":606874,"text":"That's how tiny the motions are\nthat we are now able to pull out"},{"time":610435,"text":"just by observing how light\nbounces off objects"},{"time":613678,"text":"and gets recorded by our cameras."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615814,"text":"We can recover sounds\nfrom other objects, like plants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619064,"text":"(Music: \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":627214,"text":"And we can recover speech as well."},{"time":629211,"text":"So here's a person speaking in a room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631788,"text":"Voice: Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":635991,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthat lamb was sure to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640221,"text":"Michael Rubinstein: And here's\nthat speech again recovered"},{"time":642980,"text":"just from this video\nof that same bag of chips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646254,"text":"Voice: Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":651085,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthat lamb was sure to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655944,"text":"MR: We used \"Mary Had a Little Lamb\""},{"time":658290,"text":"because those are said to be\nthe first words"},{"time":660413,"text":"that Thomas Edison spoke \ninto his phonograph in 1877."},{"time":664574,"text":"It was one of the first sound\nrecording devices in history."},{"time":667802,"text":"It basically directed the sounds\nonto a diaphragm"},{"time":671129,"text":"that vibrated a needle that essentially\nengraved the sound on tinfoil"},{"time":675208,"text":"that was wrapped around the cylinder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677483,"text":"Here's a demonstration of recording and \nreplaying sound with Edison's phonograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683426,"text":"(Video) Voice: Testing,\ntesting, one two three."},{"time":686446,"text":"Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":689859,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthe lamb was sure to go."},{"time":693528,"text":"Testing, testing, one two three."},{"time":696268,"text":"Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":700424,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthe lamb was sure to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705648,"text":"MR: And now, 137 years later,"},{"time":709665,"text":"we're able to get sound\nin pretty much similar quality"},{"time":713752,"text":"but by just watching objects\nvibrate to sound with cameras,"},{"time":717831,"text":"and we can even do that when the camera"},{"time":719765,"text":"is 15 feet away from the object,\nbehind soundproof glass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723999,"text":"So this is the sound that we were \nable to recover in that case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727219,"text":"Voice: Mary had a little lamb\nwhose fleece was white as snow,"},{"time":732513,"text":"and everywhere that Mary went,\nthe lamb was sure to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737404,"text":"MR: And of course, surveillance is\nthe first application that comes to mind."},{"time":741034,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":744029,"text":"But it might actually be useful\nfor other things as well."},{"time":748085,"text":"Maybe in the future, we'll be able\nto use it, for example,"},{"time":750925,"text":"to recover sound across space,"},{"time":753177,"text":"because sound can't travel\nin space, but light can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756753,"text":"We've only just begun exploring"},{"time":759157,"text":"other possible uses\nfor this new technology."},{"time":762176,"text":"It lets us see physical processes\nthat we know are there"},{"time":765008,"text":"but that we've never been able\nto see with our own eyes until now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768564,"text":"This is our team."},{"time":769768,"text":"Everything I showed you today\nis a result of a collaboration"},{"time":772647,"text":"with this great group\nof people you see here,"},{"time":774838,"text":"and I encourage you and welcome you\nto check out our website,"},{"time":778005,"text":"try it out yourself,"},{"time":779451,"text":"and join us in exploring\nthis world of tiny motions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782423,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784048,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}